## 1. Create a new React app

First, you will need to install the necessary dependencies for a React app, such as `react`, `react-dom`, and `react-router-dom`, which allows you to create routing in your app.
```bash
npm install react react-dom react-router-dom
```
Then, create a new directory for your app and navigate to it:
```bash
mkdir my-app
cd my-app
```
Now, run the command to initialize a new React app:
```bash
npx create-react-app my-app
```
This will create a basic React app in the `my-app` directory that you can start developing right away.

